{"abstract":"A second-generation mass storage system, MSS-II, is described. It achieves a 10-MB transfer rate into and out of the central-network mass-storage node, while preserving the illusion to users that it is simply an ordinary Unix system with an infinite supply of very fast disk space. It does so by implementing a Berkeley RAID-style file system in kernel software, by instituting striping network access, by implementing a transparent hierarchical storage manager, and by extending the concepts of file ownership and permission to removable volumes. The major software components (i.e. the high-performance file system, rapid-access storage hierarchy, volume manager, and striping network access) and file integrity are discussed. >","arxivId":null,"authors":[{"authorId":"2754390","name":"D. Tweten","url":"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2754390"}],"citationVelocity":0,"citations":[{"arxivId":null,"authors":[{"authorId":"2598521","name":"I. Adams"},{"authorId":"32576492","name":"B. A. Madden"},{"authorId":"3084648","name":"J. Frank"},{"authorId":"2011171","name":"M. Storer"},{"authorId":"1695221","name":"E. L. Miller"},{"authorId":"3151605","name":"Gene Harano"}],"doi":"10.1109/SC.2012.110","intent":[],"isInfluential":false,"paperId":"b90a6b5576d12c2c2e66442b430469cebede8eea","title":"Usage behavior of a large-scale scientific archive","url":"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/b90a6b5576d12c2c2e66442b430469cebede8eea","venue":"2012 International Conference for High Performance Computing, Networking, Storage and Analysis","year":2012},{"arxivId":null,"authors":[{"authorId":"2663652","name":"HweeHwa Pang"}],"doi":"10.1007/s005300050070","intent":["methodology"],"isInfluential":false,"paperId":"4d36de369d0695742a715b4befec792e7266c172","title":"Tertiary storage in multimedia systems: staging or direct access?","url":"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/4d36de369d0695742a715b4befec792e7266c172","venue":"Multimedia Systems","year":1997},{"arxivId":null,"auth